    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-25T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="376"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.796/193: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-25T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 25, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>842. Your 1129, October 13, 5 p.m., and 1169, October 21, 7 p.m. With respect to
                    your inquiry whether the Phillips Petroleum Company would, under certain
                    conditions, be permitted to proceed with its contract with YPF, it may be stated
                    that the manufacture of high octane gasoline requires highly specialized
                    machinery all of which for some time to come is earmarked for urgent defense
                    needs.</p>
                <p>It is accordingly evident that it will not be feasible in the near future to
                    provide Argentina with the desired manufacturing facilities irrespective of
                    whether YPF undertakes a commitment to withhold fuel from Axis airlines.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
